This lovely 1960 MGA will bring back memories of the golden era of the British roadster, knock off wire wheels, low cut doors, great exhaust notes and the wind in your hair. This is a survivor car that has been restored as needed its entire life. The car was a California car and has no rust, very uncommon for an MG of this vintage. The current owner, a British car collector, purchased this MGA from the original family about four years ago and the car has always been stored indoors.

The 1600 motor performs beautifully with the twin SU carbs singing along and all the electrics are in tip top condition, operating as they should. The 4-speed Moss transmission shifts readily through all gears, all the while giving you that unmistakable gear noise that is music to any motorcar enthusiast. The mechanicals have just been fully serviced, fresh fluids, spark plugs-wires, carburetors rebuilt, valves adjusted, new fan belt, new radiator and thermostat, brakes serviced, and a new stainless performance exhaust system has been fitted. Inside, new carpets, floor mats, and upholstery highlight the interior along with the cool MG gloss black banjo type steering wheel. A brand new soft top has been fitted as well and the hard plexiglass side curtains are in nice shape.

The body is very nice, all panel gaps are even and the paint and chrome are both in good condition showing very little wear. The Lucas tri-bar headlamps up front add a very cool retro look and the chrome rear luggage rack awaits your favorite vintage suitcase or pick nick basket. This little MGA is ready to become a loyal addition to your family and will bring you many miles of adventures and memories.
